column3: Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/6c98cca9e47ddb9c786cd3f0445175c378515e0d for binaries and test log.\nThis test script verifies pulls every time they are updated. It, however, dies sometimes and fails to test properly.  If you are waiting on a test, please check timestamps to verify that the test.log is moving at http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/cu
ACK (untested, but changes look trivial and good).\n

It appears that this does change a little bit of behavior: it's now possible to delete the last recipient. This is harmless: send will do nothing, and it's possible to add it again.\nBut to keep the same behavior I need to re-think this a bit.\n
Ignore that: that was already the case without this patch.\nPhew.\n
